Create DGE List

minCPM <- 1
minSamples <- 6

dgeList <- miR.Counts %>%
    as.data.frame() %>%
  .[rowSums(cpm(.) >= minCPM) >= minSamples,] %>%
  DGEList(
    samples = tibble(sample = colnames(.)) %>%
      left_join(samples),
    genes = rownames(.)) %>%
  calcNormFactors()

contr.matrix <- makeContrasts(
   Sham24vsUnx24 = Unx.24hr-Sham.24hr, 
   Sham48vsUnx48 = Unx.48hr-Sham.48hr, 
   Sham72vsUnx72 = Unx.72hr-Sham.72hr,
   ShamvsUnx = (Unx.24hr+Unx.72hr+Unx.48hr)-(Sham.24hr+Sham.48hr+Sham.72hr),
   Unx24vsUnx48 = Unx.48hr-Unx.24hr,
   Unx24vsUnx72 = Unx.72hr-Unx.24hr,
   Unx48vsUnx72 = Unx.72hr-Unx.48hr,
   Sham24vsSham48 = Sham.48hr-Sham.24hr,
   Sham24vsSham72 = Sham.72hr-Sham.24hr,
   Sham48vsSham72 = Sham.72hr-Sham.48hr,
   t24vst48 = (Sham.48hr+Unx.48hr)-(Unx.24hr+Sham.24hr),
   t24vst72 = (Unx.72hr+Sham.72hr)-(Unx.24hr+Sham.24hr),
   t48vst72 = (Unx.72hr+Sham.72hr)-(Unx.48hr+Sham.48hr),
   ShamvsUnx24 = (Unx.24hr)-(Sham.24hr+Sham.72hr+Sham.48hr),
   ShamvsUnx48 = (Unx.48hr)-(Sham.24hr+Sham.72hr+Sham.48hr),
   ShamvsUnx72 = (Unx.72hr)-(Sham.24hr+Sham.72hr+Sham.48hr),
   levels = colnames(design))

Estimation of sample weights

The approach taken for DGE analysis was to use voom-precision weights in order to allow for modelling using Normally distributed data. Sample-level weights were estimated as part of this process, with all samples normally being considered as belonging to the same treatment group, to allow more conservative estimates.

v <- voomWithQualityWeights(dgeList, design, plot=FALSE)

Sample weights after voom transformation. The idealised equal weighting of \(w = 1\) is shown as the dashed line.

Means (x-axis) and variances (y-axis) of each gene are plotted to show the dependence between the two before voom is applied to the data (left panel) and how the trend is removed after voom precision weights are applied to the data (right panel)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
v2 <- voom(dgeList, design, plot=TRUE)
v2fit <-lmFit(v2, design)
e2fit <-eBayes(v2fit)
plotSA(e2fit, main="Final model: Mean-variance trend")

Strict Comparison between groups

tau <- log2(1)

For the comparison between groups, a null hypothesis was tested using a range of values, instead of the point value zero, i.e.

\[ H_0: -\tau < \Delta \mu < \tau \\ Vs. \\ H_A: | \Delta \mu | > \tau \]

The default value used in the function treat() is \(\tau = \log_2 1.2\) and for this analysis, \(\tau = \log_2 1\) was chosen as a suitable value.

alpha <- 0.05

tfit <- lmFit(v,design) %>% 
  contrasts.fit(contr.matrix) %>%
  treat(lfc = tau)

This gave the number of genes considered as DE between the comparison groups with Bonferroni adjusted P-value < 0.05.

summary(decideTests(tfit))
##        Sham24vsUnx24 Sham48vsUnx48 Sham72vsUnx72 ShamvsUnx Unx24vsUnx48
## Down               0             6             0         7           57
## NotSig           552           528           547       514          460
## Up                 0            18             5        31           35
##        Unx24vsUnx72 Unx48vsUnx72 Sham24vsSham48 Sham24vsSham72 Sham48vsSham72
## Down             77            1             72             63              1
## NotSig          414          549            392            425            551
## Up               61            2             88             64              0
##        t24vst48 t24vst72 t48vst72 ShamvsUnx24 ShamvsUnx48 ShamvsUnx72
## Down         89       89        1         450         453         455
## NotSig      354      349      547          86          82          83
## Up          109      114        4          16          17          14
topTables <- colnames(contr.matrix) %>%
  sapply(function(x){
  topTreat(tfit, coef = x, n = Inf) %>%
      as_tibble() %>%
      rownames_to_column("No.") %>%
      arrange(P.Value) %>% 
      mutate(DE= adj.P.Val < alpha,
             Status = case_when(
      DE ==TRUE & logFC < 0 ~ "Down",
      DE == TRUE & logFC > 0 ~ "Up"),
      Status = ifelse(is.na(Status), "NotSig", Status))}, simplify = FALSE)

My Boxplot

boxplotVW <- cpm(dgeList, log=TRUE, prior.count = 3)[common_DE,] %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("gene_id") %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    gather(key = "sample", value = "CPM", -gene_id) %>%
    mutate(CPM = CPM + 1) %>%
    left_join(dgeList$samples) %>%
  mutate(treatment = fct_relevel(treatment, "Sham","Unx")) %>%
  mutate(group = fct_relevel(group, "Sham.24hr","Sham.48hr","Sham.72hr","Unx.24hr","Unx.48hr","Unx.72hr")) %>%
    ggplot(aes(group, CPM, fill = treatment)) +

Retrieve interactions between a set of miRNAs and a set of genes

DE_miRNA_up <-topTables$Sham48vsUnx48 %>% dplyr::filter(DE==TRUE & Status=="Up") %>% .$genes
DE_entrez.dn <- topTablesRNA$Sham48vsUnx48 %>% dplyr::filter(DE==TRUE & Status=="Down") %>% .$entrezid %>% unlist()

# search all tables & top 10% predictions
regulation <- get_multimir(org     = "mmu",
                         mirna   = DE_miRNA_up,
                         target  = DE_entrez.dn,
                         table   = "all",
                         summary = TRUE,
                         predicted.cutoff.type = "p",
                         predicted.cutoff      = 10,
                         use.tibble = TRUE)
